------------------------------------------------------------------------
The pst-perspective package --- orthogonal parallel projection
Maintained by Thomas S\"{o}ll E-mail: thomas.soell@lehrer.uka.de
Released under the LaTeX Project Public License
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The package pst-perspective draw an orthogonal parallel projection with an arbitrarily chosen angle and a variable shortening factor.
The points first get projected orthogonally to the base line, and therefrom they get transformed with an arbitrarily chosen angle and shortened.


Installation
------------

Copy the files pst-perspective.tex and pst-perspective.sty in your
LaTeX-input folder and than tex-hash. Now you can use it with
usepackage{pst-perspective}.

The package requires recent versions of pstricks and pst-node.
